and I'm not
gonna stand here

14:50.157 --> 14:51.691
and tell you about
the struggles I've faced

14:51.724 --> 14:54.995
as a recovering alcoholic with
a dream of becoming a lawyer.

14:57.664 --> 14:59.466
Okay.

15:02.402 --> 15:06.139
What I am going to tell you
is that...

15:07.975 --> 15:10.010
I am your worst nightmare.

15:11.544 --> 15:14.514
I have worked at this restaurant
for 11 years,

15:14.547 --> 15:17.350
and I know where all the bodies
are buried.

15:17.384 --> 15:19.652
I know that your
locally sourced, organic,

15:19.686 --> 15:22.289
grass-fed beef is only
one of those things.

15:22.322 --> 15:26.293
I know that several of our
busboys live in the basement,

15:26.326 --> 15:28.095
along with assorted vermin.

15:31.498 --> 15:33.600
And I know that
we served the tip

15:33.633 --> 15:36.003
of Paul's finger
in last week's ceviche.

15:38.005 --> 15:41.574
I could go on, but, uh, I think
I've painted a picture.

15:43.543 --> 15:46.379
So, you fire me and all of this
goes on Yelp.

15:46.413 --> 15:48.148
Or you put me back on the books

15:48.181 --> 15:50.517
and that nice, pretty
four-and-a-half star rating

15:50.550 --> 15:51.951
stays right where it is.

15:54.021 --> 15:55.188
Works for me.

15:58.258 --> 15:59.592
See that, Geoffrey?

15:59.626 --> 16:02.195
That's how you make it
to Sacramento.

16:03.630 --> 16:05.098
Oh.

16:05.132 --> 16:07.100
I might be a little late
tomorrow.

16:07.134 --> 16:08.501
We'll see how it goes.

16:19.612 --> 16:21.214
Hey, Bonnie.

16:22.515 --> 16:23.683
Hello.

16:25.485 --> 16:27.520
So, um...

16:27.554 --> 16:29.189
Adam kicked me out.

16:29.222 --> 16:30.457
Yeah.

16:30.490 --> 16:31.791
He told me.

16:31.824 --> 16:33.326
What's the big deal?

16:33.360 --> 16:35.295
I got high once.

16:35.328 --> 16:37.364
The big deal is
you're an addict.

16:37.397 --> 16:39.099
And your life is
not gonna get better

16:39.132 --> 16:40.667
until you deal with it.

16:44.371 --> 16:45.605
Can I stay here?

16:47.507 --> 16:49.676
Nope.

16:49.709 --> 16:52.145
Seriously?

16:52.179 --> 16:54.514
What am I supposed to do?
Sleep in my car?

16:54.547 --> 16:56.383
I've done it.

16:56.416 --> 16:57.817
Little tip: park at Walmart.

16:57.850 --> 16:59.419
They won't kick you out.

16:59.452 --> 17:02.422
Bonnie, I'm your brother.

17:02.455 --> 17:06.393
I know... and I love you.

17:24.311 --> 17:25.845
There are a few announcements
before we begin.

17:25.878 --> 17:27.547
The community center has
asked us not to smoke

17:27.580 --> 17:29.449
on the property,
and not to park

17:29.482 --> 17:34.654
in the reserved spaces on the
north side of the building.

17:34.687 --> 17:37.290
I got your text.

17:37.324 --> 17:38.691
You did the right thing.

17:38.725 --> 17:40.593
It doesn't really
feel like it.

17:40.627 --> 17:42.862
I know.

17:42.895 --> 17:45.798
Would you kick me out if
I started using again?

17:45.832 --> 17:49.669
I did.
You just don't remember.

17:50.803 --> 17:52.672
If it helps,

17:52.705 --> 17:55.642
I never thought you were gonna
get sober, but you did.

17:55.675 --> 17:56.843
Back at ya.

17:56.876 --> 17:58.278
MEETING LEADER:
Please take a moment

17:58.311 --> 17:59.146
to silence your cell phones

17:59.179 --> 18:00.380
and out of respect
for the speaker...

18:00.413 --> 18:01.681
How's Adam dealing with it?

18:01.714 --> 18:04.651
He turned it over to
his higher power.

18:04.684 --> 18:06.719
*

18:09.722 --> 18:12.725
White Russian.
Keep 'em coming.

18:14.761 --> 18:15.895
Rough day?

18:15.928 --> 18:17.897
Ugh. Just this woman
who works for me.

18:17.930 --> 18:19.832
She's been busting my balls
all week.

18:21.268 --> 18:22.835
I hear ya.

18:22.869 --> 18:25.238
Bartender, put his drinks
on my tab.

18:25.272 --> 18:26.706
Hey.
Hey.

18:26.739 --> 18:27.707
Who's your friend?

18:27.740 --> 18:28.741
Ah, just another man

18:28.775 --> 18:30.477
with an ice pack
down his shorts.

18:35.915 --> 18:37.617
So, how you doin'?

18:37.650 --> 18:40.453
I'm okay, I just feel bad
about Ray.

18:40.487 --> 18:42.489
For what it's worth,
it means a lot to me

18:42.522 --> 18:44.224
that you tried
to help my brother.

18:44.257 --> 18:46.659
I like the guy.

18:46.693 --> 18:48.761
Think I'll get
my two grand back?

18:48.795 --> 18:51.264
Mm, you're adorable.

18:51.298 --> 18:52.665
Mm.
Tell you what,

18:52.699 --> 18:53.633
this round's on me.

18:53.666 --> 18:55.635
He'll have another beer.

18:55.668 --> 18:56.836
I'll take a Sprite.

18:56.869 --> 18:59.172
Coming up.
Wait a minute.

18:59.206 --> 19:01.308
Bonnie?

19:01.341 --> 19:03.243
Oh, my God.

19:03.276 --> 19:04.877
Frankie, is that you?

19:04.911 --> 19:06.679
I heard you were dead.

19:06.713 --> 19:09.349
Heard the same thing about you.

19:09.382 --> 19:11.218
You used to drink in here?

19:11.251 --> 19:12.952
No. Frankie and I
spent a weekend

19:12.985 --> 19:14.854
in the hull
of a ship and...

19:14.887 --> 19:16.556
You know what?

19:16.589 --> 19:17.824
Story for another time.

